PN,31507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1782371887
OL,3,CKeir Starmer to face PMQs for first
OL,4,Ctime since he announced resignation
OL,6,FElsewhere, crossbench peer Jim O'Neill
OL,7,F` who has been advising Mr Burnham `
OL,8,Ftold the Guardian he wanted to see a
OL,9,Fnew, independent body set up so that
OL,10,Fextra money could be spent on
OL,11,Finfrastructure while remaining within
OL,12,FLabour's fiscal rules.
OL,14,FThe body could follow the model of the
OL,15,FOffice for Budget Responsibility, he
OL,16,Fsaid, allowing for billions more to be
OL,17,Fspent on boosting big transport and
OL,18,Fpublic works projects.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1782371887
OL,3,CKeir Starmer to face PMQs for first
OL,4,Ctime since he announced resignation
OL,6,FThough Mr Burnham is the most likely
OL,7,Fcandidate to succeed Sir Keir, other
OL,8,FMPs continue to be discussed as
OL,9,Fpotential leadership contenders.
OL,11,FFormer defence minister Al Carns, who
OL,12,Ffollowed Mr Healey out the door this
OL,13,Fmonth, told Newsnight he was "pretty
OL,14,Fserious" about launching a leadership
OL,15,Fbid.
OL,17,FHe added he wanted to see the policies
OL,18,FMr Burnham was going to champion,
OL,19,Ftelling the BBC programme: "We need to
OL,20,Fsee that material before I can make a
OL,21,Fdecision to back anyone."
OL,26,@uD@^OUvD@HO]{D@\OU}D@YO]
